projects.title: SPIN Model For HAVIK-Mortgages
projects.description:
Client			:   ABN AMRO 
Technology		:   Java1.5, JAX-WS Web services, WSDL, Maven, Copybook, RAD

           Project Description
HAVIK is the front end application of ABN-Amro to provide customer with Mortgages related advices.
It’s a .net application developed by a third party vendor called TJIP.
In order to provide data to this application the bank has adopted a new model based on the Service Oriented Architecture called the Spider or Spin model.
It’s basically an architecture based purely on web-services where the third party vendor has access to a single web-service which in turn connects to multiple web-services to fetch and provide data from ABN-Amro databases. 
As the IT solutions partner of ABN-Amro the role of TCS has been to build the services and integrate the application within the ABN-Amro network

         Responsibilities:
•	Involved in all phases of SDLC 
•	Responsible for developing the technical design to implement the SPIN model within ABN-Amro environment.
•	Developing the SPIN Web-Services.
•	Involved in build and deployment activities using Maven2.
•	Responsible for testing up to System test environment.
•	Providing support to iST (integration system testing) and iFAT (integration Functional Acceptance Testing) teams.
•	Involved in providing production support.

projects.title: Uniform Advies Application (UAD)
projects.description:
Client			:   ABN AMRO 
Organization		:   TATA CONSULTANCY SERVICES
Technology		:   Java1.5, Struts 1.3, BIB2 (Custom framework), JAX-WS Web services, 	WSDL, ANT, DB2, XSL, JSP, XSLT, AJAX, RAD

           Project Description
The main aim of the UAD application is to provide the client with investments related advice and helping him with his investments portfolio. (Mostly sell/buy advices on stocks, bonds, equities etc.)
A third party vendor (IDMS) provides the actual advice and the role of TCS has been to integrate the IDMS tool within ABN-Amro environment.

         Responsibilities:
•	Involved in all phases of SDLC and development from scratch.
•	Singlehandedly responsible for developing the front end screens for the application using XSLT, JSP, JavaScript and based on customized struts framework (BIB2).
•	Developing the backend java services.
•	Involved in build and deployment activities using Ant.
•	Providing support to iST (integration system testing) and iFAT (integration Functional Acceptance Testing) teams.
•	Implementing CR’s
•	Involved in providing production support.
